xy plot data, plus lowess fit (unless just 'p'oints). Usage:

  r-fu xy datfile out.pdf
  ... | r-fu xy - out.pdf

where the 'datfile' or standard input contains two columns of X and Y
data (R is picky about input, so leading and trailing whitespace may
need to be trimmed, and a single space used to delimit the data).

An optional third argument allows the plot type to be specified (default
is 'b'oth 'p'oints and 'l'ines):

  r-fu xy datfile out.pdf p

